 core masses\nlarger than predicted by our models. This may be possible if the progenitors\nwere fast rotators on the main sequence. If further study confirms this\ninterpretation, a fast initial rotation would be a strong signature of the\npeculiarity of extreme second-generation stars in GCs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Jul 2015 10:17:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-22"}
